<TITLE> DMC may reopen this week: minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 5 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka Medical College that closed after BCL factions clashed Tuesday may reopen this week, the health minister said Sunday. "DMC will be reopened soon," AFM Ruhul Haque Haque told reporters after a meeting with the principals of medical colleges and hospital directors in the noon. "We hope so," he said when asked if the premier medical college would open this week. In the wake of clashes between two factions of ruling Awami League's student front, the DMC was shut down sine die. The meeting decided that 'hospital service week' will be observed countrywide from April 7 to April 13 to improve the quality of service. Three committees have been formed comprising local elected representatives that will work to better manage hospitals and ensure quality of service at public hospitals, the minister added. "I'll go to the DMC myself and sit there from April 7 onwards to help uplift the quality of service rendered there," Haque said. Any irregularities reported from any hospital will be dealt with as per rules and regulations, he added. Proposals were made in the meeting to increase charges at the hospitals, Haque said and added such an important decision had to be made after more detailed discussions by all stakeholders. bdne
